snippet.textDisplay: I‚Äôm not surprised that the iPhone MagSafe could disable pacemakers. A teenage girl figured out that the magnets for the smart covers for the first couple generations of iPads could disable pacemakers if a person took a nap with their iPad on their chest. The new iPhone MagSafe devices have a higher density of magnetic flux (flow of magnetism) so it would take less time to disable a pacemaker. Doctors use strong (2‚Äùx2‚Äùx1‚Äù) non neodymium magnets to disable pacemakers. My grandfather who was a doctor had a couple of these magnets on his fridge that were labeled with pacemaker warnings.
